This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for brain decoding using functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) data. The proposed model involves convolutional neural networks (CNNs) with temporal filters and spatial pooling layers, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of unsupervised learning with autoencoders suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses hyper-parameter tuning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
